<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Forelorn:
[B]Will the new level expansion mabye allow shadow knights access to weapons equal to the paladin class?
Will the expansion create the ability for the shadow knights to get the good necro spells instead of a small number of unappealing spells?
I found that the array of spells given to me were not very useful in comparison to the other necro spells I had seen at the same spell level.
I noticed the add on to the physically weak erudite to the list of shadow knight classes. I was wondering if they will allow us access to ALL of the spells at the lower level necromancer spell array.

My first character was a human shadow knight. I picked him because the thought of being a 50/50 hybrid with a warrior and an "evil" casting class appealed to me. I figured that the class would be powerful, sacrificing access to the "good" cities and a large chunk of my experience for that power. I now have realized I picked a 50% warrior and a 10% necromancer hybrid, and in doing so I sacrificed strength, stamina, agility, dexterity, and intellegence. The fighting skills of the caster prominent SKs  (DEs and now erudites) are horrible. The ogres and trolls are strong physically, but terrible casters and they are disgusting. I picked human because I had hoped being human would offset the loss of experience and it does help. Overall, I look at the flip side of the shadow knight, the paladin. The stats on the dwarf paladin are insanely good, the spells they have are the choice cleric spells, and their special ability lay hands is unbeliveably useful. Harm touch? 10xlevel+1 damage that is resisted half the time against a full HP restore? When I can see a shadow knight and a paladin fight each other and the fight come even close, then I will be happy. The weapons of the shadow knight class do not even begin to compare with the array of weapons the paladins wield. I love this game, I like playing an eveil melee class, but I am getting tired of shouting "shadow knight looking for group" and watching classes of the same level getting picked over me. I would enjoy feedback from someone at verant, because I have been sending feedback using the in-game function nearly once a week. It is late and I am tired. Thanks for hearing me out.  [/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
